  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0b95\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0b9f \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Special Notification of Ministry of Power",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Power has requested the public that the last digit of the vehicle number plate and the token system will not be valid from August 1 and that they should not gather at fuel filling stations on that day to avoid unnecessary congestion.",
        "The Ministry also announced that the National Fuel Permit QR system will be implemented from that day.",
        "The Ministry indicated that evidence and information regarding illegal fuel hoarders can be sent to 0742123123 and if they are identified as suspects, their QR code will be invalidated.",
        "It has also been informed that vehicles which cannot be registered through the QR system through the chassis number will be allowed to register using the vehicle annual revenue permit number.",
        "Also, all autos have to register at police stations and provide details of the nearest petrol station allotted to them, it has been said.",
        "Owners of fuel-requiring equipment have been advised to register with their Divisional Secretariat at the designated filling station where they intend to obtain fuel.",
        "While priority will be given to public transport, fuel allocation for buses will be decided taking into account their route clearance and number of kilometers travelled, the ministry said.",
        "It is mentioned that the transport council depot will supply all the fuel required for school transport services, staff transport, industries, tourism related vehicles, ambulances and other approved services.",
        "However, all petrol stations have been instructed to give priority to ambulances and provide unlimited fuel to them."
      ],
